[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/two_club"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH opens 2\C and NORTH responds 2\D showing fewer than 8 points.

SOUTH bids 2NT with a 23 point balanced hand.

NORTH has enough points to bid 3NT, but with two 4-card Major suits bids 3\C Stayman instead. SOUTH 
won't confuse this as the second negative since that bid isn't used after a 2NT rebid.

So SOUTH shows her 4-card \H suit and NORTH bids 4\H.}

